    "The 'first light' principle: the melanopsin-containing ipRGC cells in the eye need to detect the rate of light increase (dawn signal) as well as absolute lux levels — watching the sunrise (not just being in daylight) produces the strongest circadian entrainment signal available.",
    "Chronotherapy for mood disorders exploits circadian biology: deliberately keeping a patient awake for 36 hours ('sleep deprivation therapy') produces immediate antidepressant effects in 60% of treatment-resistant patients, driven by acute resetting of disrupted circadian phase.",
    "Post-lunch dip in alertness is not caused by eating per se but by a circadian-programmed drop in core body temperature and SCN alerting signal that occurs between 1–3pm independent of meal timing.",
