    "The 'T-cycle experiment' (altering artificial day length) shows that human performance on all measures tracks with the circadian phase, not wall clock time — the SCN determines your physiology, not your schedule.",
    "Jet lag recovery follows the 1-hour-per-day rule in the eastward direction and 1.5 hours per day westward, because the human clock's natural 24.2-hour period makes westward phase delay neurologically easier than eastward phase advance.",
