    "The 'warm-up' principle for cognition has a circadian basis: analytical reasoning peaks 2–4 hours after waking for morning chronotypes, meaning the first 60–90 minutes of waking are better suited to routine, physical, or creative-intuitive tasks.",
    "Phosphatidic acid (from soy lecithin) activates mTOR signaling in a circadian-gated manner, with maximal anabolic response to resistance exercise occurring in the late afternoon for most chronotypes — aligning strength training with this window optimizes adaptive signaling.",
