    "The 'phase advance' protocol (morning light + evening darkness + earlier social schedule + morning exercise) is the gold-standard non-pharmacological chronotherapy for night owls, advancing sleep timing by 2–3 hours within 3–4 weeks.",
    "Circadian gene mutations (familial advanced sleep phase syndrome — FASPS) produce 'extreme larks' who fall asleep at 7pm and wake at 4am regardless of social schedule — this demonstrates that chronotype is a literal genetic phenotype, not a character trait.",
    "The liver's circadian clock optimizes lipid metabolism across the day — consuming the majority of dietary fat in the morning (when hepatic fat oxidation is highest) produces more efficient fat metabolism than identical intake consumed at night.",
    "Thermosensitive TRP channels in the skin directly signal temperature to the SCN, explaining why environmental temperature is a more powerful circadian zeitgeber than meal timing — cold morning showers and warm evening baths both provide targeted circadian signals.",
    "Cortisol's immunosuppressive effect during the day prevents excessive inflammatory responses to daily microtrauma — taking anti-inflammatory supplements in the morning (when cortisol is already high) produces redundant immunosuppression and may blunt the normal cortisol rhythm.",
