    "Tart cherry juice (240ml twice daily) contains both melatonin and tryptophan in concentrations shown to increase urinary melatonin metabolites and extend sleep duration by 25–34 minutes in controlled trials — the most evidence-backed food-based sleep intervention.",
    "Circadian disruption impairs the 'resolution' of the inflammatory response — not just its onset — meaning disrupted sleepers develop chronic low-grade inflammation not because they produce more inflammatory signals, but because they fail to turn them off.",
    "For individuals with DSPD (Delayed Sleep Phase Disorder), morning light therapy (10,000 lux for 30 minutes at wake time) combined with blue-light blocking after 6pm produces greater clock advancement than either intervention alone.",
