    "The 'default interpretation effect' shows that complex concepts are automatically interpreted through the lens of the learner's most activated mental model — deliberately activating the correct schema before learning new material reduces misinterpretation.",
    "Sentence complexity (nested subordinate clauses) increases parsing load on the phonological loop and working memory — simplifying the grammatical structure of your notes and communications reduces the cognitive tax on every future reader.",
    "The 'spotlight suppressor' (how the brain inhibits unattended stimuli) operates through lateral inhibition in the thalamus — training this mechanism via selective listening or focused visual tasks measurably reduces distractibility across all sensory modalities.",
