    "Acetylcholine directly modulates the signal-to-noise ratio in the cortex — when ACh is high (focused attention), cortical representations sharpen and distractors are filtered; when ACh is low (fatigue), all stimuli are processed with equal weight.",
    "Stress produces an inverted-U relationship with memory — moderate stress (eustress) via cortisol and norepinephrine enhances encoding; chronic or excessive stress destroys hippocampal architecture via glucocorticoid toxicity.",
    "Temporal discounting — the tendency to prefer earlier over later rewards — is steeper when cognitive load is high, meaning people make worse long-term decisions when they're cognitively taxed; reducing load before financial or life decisions measurably improves their quality.",
