    "'Transcriptional homeostasis' in dopamine neurons means that chronic dopaminergic over-stimulation triggers compensatory reduction in receptor density and dopamine synthesis — the tolerance effect is not psychological weakness but a physically measured molecular adaptation.",
    "PFC dopamine specifically gates whether attention is driven 'top-down' (by goals) or 'bottom-up' (by salient stimuli) — low PFC dopamine causes attention to be captured by whatever is most salient in the environment, while optimal PFC dopamine allows intentional control of attentional focus.",
