    "The 'adenosine index' — the ratio of waking hours to prior sleep hours — predicts objective cognitive performance better than any single self-report measure; tracking this ratio via consistent logging provides a non-genetic predictor of your daily cognitive peak.",
    "Circadian regulation of synaptic glutamate signaling creates a daily cycle of excitability — the post-dawn excitability peak in the cortex is a neurological 'amplifier' for incoming information, making early morning learning neurologically privileged for information that benefits from high-excitability encoding.",
    "Lutein and zeaxanthin (from leafy greens and eggs) accumulate in the macula and filter high-energy blue light before it reaches the ipRGCs — adequate macular pigment may modestly buffer the circadian-disrupting effects of evening screen use.",
    "The 'cortisol-melatonin handoff' — the evening crossover where cortisol drops below melatonin rising — defines the practical start of the biological night; detecting this crossover in yourself (via symptom awareness or wearable tracking) provides a personally calibrated bedtime signal.",
    "The 'metabolic clock' in adipose tissue follows a 24-hour cycle of lipolysis (fat release) and lipogenesis (fat storage) — chronically eating outside the active metabolic window shifts adipose clock genes toward lipogenesis, producing fat accumulation independent of caloric intake.",
    "Time-restricted eating at 8am–6pm (aligned with the active phase) improves glycemic variability, reduces inflammatory markers, and improves sleep quality simultaneously — the circadian alignment of calorie intake is the single variable that distinguishes TRE from simple caloric restriction.",
    "The 'photoreceptor mosaic' in the retina contains three types of cone photoreceptors (S, M, L) and melanopsin-containing ipRGC — all five photoreceptor types contribute to circadian entrainment, making full-spectrum natural light superior to any single-wavelength artificial circadian intervention.",
    "The 'circadian immune surveillance' cycle deploys NK cells and T-cells according to a 24-hour schedule — surgery performed at specific circadian phases (studies indicate mid-morning for most procedures) produces measurably better outcomes and fewer post-operative complications.",
    "The 'sleep pressure asymptote' — the maximum achievable sleep pressure — is genetically set and determines how much total sleep benefit you can accumulate — individuals with higher sleep pressure asymptotes show steeper cognitive performance declines from equivalent sleep loss and faster recovery after recovery sleep.",

