    "The 'attention restoration theory' prediction about awe: experiences of awe (perceived vastness + accommodation of prior schemas) produce the most powerful directed-attention recovery of any positive emotion — even 10 minutes of awe-inducing nature exposure or content produces measurably better subsequent focused attention than equivalent neutral relaxation.",
    "The 'dual-coding' advantage is maximal when verbal and visual representations are complementary rather than redundant — the most powerful note-taking strategy combines precise verbal definitions with idiosyncratic spatial visualizations that encode different (not identical) aspects of the same concept.",
